<div><h3>MGMT 4800 - Strategic Decision Making </h3>  <hr>This course utilizes concepts from strategic management, economics, finance, operations, marketing, and management in an integrative approach to strategic decision making. Students learn tools and frameworks for assessing industry competitive factors, industry environments, and external environments that include economic, legal-political, technological, socio-cultural, and natural environment forces. The objectives of the course are to assess the impact of these factors on management decisions and organizational competitiveness and long term success. Emphasis is placed on the development and growth of critical thinking skills using case studies and research projects.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Students must have 6 units completed in the MBA program prior to taking this course.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Fall and Spring semesters<br><br></div>		</td>
